column5: I'm sitting here scratching the b/c and can't remember where I found it before.  There used to be a Lake Simcoe map that had the depths marked and when you hovered over a spot, clicked the mouse, it would put up a little flag up.  Then you clicked on the flag and it would give you the GPS location.  Any idea where to find it.  Thanks.
That was easy. Google is your friend. lol  http://www.lakesimcoeoutdoors.com/lakemapscharts.php
Already tried that one, it I can't get the GPS option on it, thanks though.  And the last thing you want to do is click the big green download button.
